UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1110
1 AN ACT proposing to amend the Constitution of Kentucky relating to sessions of
2 the General Assembly.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. Are you in favor of amending the present Constitution of Kentucky
5 to add a new section allowing the General Assembly to establish the date a regular
6 session shall end, and to meet in regular session for no more than twelve additional days
7 during any calendar year if convened by a Joint Proclamation of the President of the
8 Senate and the Speaker of the House of Representatives?
9 SECTION 2. IT IS PROPOSED THAT A NEW SECTION BE ADDED TO
10 THE CONSTITUTION OF KENTUCKY TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
11 (1) Notwithstanding the dates certain in Section 42 of this Constitution, a
12 regular session shall end on the date established by law by the General Assembly
13 unless another date shall be agreed upon by three-fifths of all members elected to each
14 House.
15 (2) In addition to regular sessions, the General Assembly may be convened by
16 Joint Proclamation of the President of the Senate and the Speaker of the House of
17 Representatives in no more than two additional sessions for no more than twelve total
18 legislative days annually, during which it may adjourn from time to time.
19 Section 3. This amendment shall be submitted to the voters of the
20 Commonwealth for their ratification or rejection at the time and in the manner provided
21 for under Sections 256 and 257 of the Constitution, KRS 118.415, and Sections 4 and 5
22 of this Act.
23 Section 4. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS 118.415 to the contrary, the
24 Secretary of State shall cause the entirety of the question in Section 1 of this Act and the
25 entirety of the proposed amendment to the Constitution of Kentucky contained in Section
26 2 of this Act to be published at least one time in a newspaper of general circulation
27 published in this state, and shall also cause to be published at the same time and in the
