UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1110
1 same manner the fact that the amendment will be submitted to the voters for their
2 acceptance or rejection at the next regular election at which members of the General
3 Assembly are to be voted for. The publication required by this section and KRS 118.415
4 shall be made no later than the first Tuesday in August preceding the election at which
5 the amendment is to be voted on.
6 Section 5. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS 118.415 to the contrary, the
7 Secretary of State, not later than the second Monday after the second Tuesday in August
8 preceding the next regular election at which members of the General Assembly are to be
9 chosen in a year in which there is not an election for President and Vice President of the
10 United States, or not later than the Thursday after the first Tuesday in September
11 preceding a regular election in a year in which there is an election for President and Vice
12 President of the United States, shall certify the entirety of the question in Section 1 of this
13 Act and the entirety of the proposed amendment to the Constitution of Kentucky
14 contained in Section 2 of this Act to the county clerk of each county, and the county clerk
15 shall have the entirety of the question and the amendment, as so certified, indicated on
16 the ballots provided to the voters in paper or electronic form as applicable to the voting
17 machines in use in each county or precinct.
